    <brief sctype="array">
      <brief sctype="string">Format Control enables you to execute additional operations at run time.</brief>
      <brief sctype="string"/>
      <brief sctype="string">Incident Management, Change Management, Database Manager, and Report Writer use Format Control.</brief>
      <brief sctype="string"/>
      <brief sctype="string">Using Format Control, you can:</brief>
      <brief sctype="string">- Specify the processes to run and when to run them, on any form or table from within a Format Control record itself.</brief>
      <brief sctype="string">- Associate a Format Control record with a form defined for a table or a database table name.</brief>
      <brief sctype="string">- Create a different Format Control record for each different form (or view) of a database table.</brief>
      <brief sctype="string"/>
      <brief sctype="string">You can only associate one Format Control record with the database table itself.</brief>
    </brief>
    <detail sctype="array">
      <detail sctype="string">At run time, the Format Control record associated with a form runs, if it exists.</detail>
      <detail sctype="string"/>
      <detail sctype="string">If there is no Format Control for the form, the Format Control record associated with the table name runs, if it exists.</detail>
      <detail sctype="string"/>
      <detail sctype="string">Format Control sequence:</detail>
      <detail sctype="string"/>
      <detail sctype="string">1. Initializations</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">2. Queries</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">3. Calculations</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">4. Validations</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">5. Sequentially Numbered Fields</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">6. Subroutines</detail>
    </detail>
